\end_layout

\end_inset

 document is as follows.
 We want:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
A variable authentication token instead of (or in addition to) web cookies,
 for resistance to BEAST, CRIME, and other adaptive chosen plaintext active
 attacks on TLS.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
The ability to explicitly logout and destroy all session state even if the
 session has been compromised, assuming there is no Man In The Browser (MITB).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
The ability to manage sessions.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
The ability to negotiate replay protection.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Cryptographic binding (
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

channel binding
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 
\begin_inset Flex EntityXRef
status collapsed

\begin_layout Plain Layout
RFC5056
\end_layout

\end_inset

) to the lower transport layer (TLS, where available).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Cryptographic binding to the user authentication mechanisms (where the authentic
ation mechanism can export a secret value).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
The ability to use HTTP/Negotiate 
